title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Generate a Wayang plan for a query that calculates total revenue per nation within the region ‘EUROPE’. Revenue is defined as the sum of l_extendedprice * (1 - l_discount) for all lineitems where the customer and supplier belong to the same nation. Join the tables customer, orders, lineitem, supplier, nation, and region through their respective foreign keys. Only include orders placed in the year 1995. Filter for r_name = 'EUROPE'. Group the results by nation name and order the output by revenue in descending order. Output in textfile.

operations.table: (SELECT r_regionkey FROM region WHERE r_name = 'EUROPE') as X

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val k = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; k != null }

operations.table: (SELECT n_nationkey, n_name, n_regionkey FROM nation) as X

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val nationKey = r.getField(1).asInstanceOf[Int]; val nationName = r.getField(2).toString; (nationKey, nationName) }

operations.table: (SELECT o_orderkey, o_custkey, o_orderdate FROM orders WHERE EXTRACT(YEAR FROM o_orderdate) = 1995) as X
(SELECT l_orderkey, l_suppkey, l_extendedprice, l_discount FROM lineitem) as X
(SELECT s_suppkey, s_nationkey FROM supplier) as X

operations.thisKeyUdf: (t: (Int, Int, java.sql.Date, Int, Int, Double, Double)) => t._4

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val nationName = r.getField(7).toString; val ext = r.getField(5).asInstanceOf[Double]; val disc = r.getField(6).asInstanceOf[Double]; val revenue = ext * (1.0 - disc); (nationName, revenue) }

log.thoughts: I constructed a plan that filters European regions, derives Europe nations, then joins orders, lineitem, customer (via nation), supplier (via nation) and computes revenue for orders in 1995. The results are grouped by nation name and ordered by total revenue descending, finally written to a text file.

title: Class: PlanMapper Mapped plan finalized for execution

data.table: (SELECT n_nationkey, n_name, n_regionkey FROM (SELECT n_nationkey, n_name, n_regionkey FROM nation) as X) as X

data.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val nationKey = r.getField(1).asInstanceOf[Int]; val nationName = r.getField(2).toString; (nationKey, nationName) }

data.table: (SELECT o_orderkey, o_custkey, o_orderdate FROM (SELECT o_orderkey, o_custkey, o_orderdate FROM orders WHERE EXTRACT(YEAR FROM o_orderdate) = 1995) as X) as X
(SELECT l_orderkey, l_suppkey, l_extendedprice, l_discount FROM (SELECT l_orderkey, l_suppkey, l_extendedprice, l_discount FROM lineitem) as X) as X
(SELECT s_suppkey, s_nationkey FROM (SELECT s_suppkey, s_nationkey FROM supplier) as X) as X

data.thisKeyUdf: (t: (Int, Int, java.sql.Date, Int, Int, Double, Double)) => t._4

data.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val nationName = r.getField(7).toString; val ext = r.getField(5).asInstanceOf[Double]; val disc = r.getField(6).asInstanceOf[Double]; val revenue = ext * (1.0 - disc); (nationName, revenue) }
